${\footnote Mouse}
+{\footnote 1}
K{\footnote Mouse;}
\pard \plain \brdrb \cf12 \fs24 \b
\{bmc IDF20234.bmp\} Mouse\par
\pard \plain \cf0 \fs20
{\uldb Controls}{\v 20121}\par
\par
\{bmc IDF20237.bmp\} \tab \b \i mouse position in horizontal direction \i0 \b0 \par
\{bmc IDF20238.bmp\} \tab \b \i mouse position in vertical direction \i0 \b0 \par
\par
The elements of the \b \i mouse positions \i0 \b0 serve to find out the current position of the mouse cursor. They return a numeric value related to the lower left sheet corner. The coordinates may also be situated outside the sheet boundaries. By using the elements as commands the position of the mouse cursor can be set.\par
\par
\{bmc IDF20235.bmp\} \tab \b \i left mouse button is held \i0 \b0 \par
\{bmc IDF20236.bmp\} \tab \b \i right mouse button is held \i0 \b0 \par
\par
The \b \i mouse button is held \i0 \b0 elements return the logic flag informing that the relevant mouse button is pressed and held.\par
\par
\{bmc IDF20358.bmp\} \tab \b \i click by left mouse button \i0 \b0 \par
\{bmc IDF20359.bmp\} \tab \b \i click by right mouse button \i0 \b0 \par
\{bmc IDF20360.bmp\} \tab \b \i double click by left mouse button \i0 \b0 \par
\{bmc IDF20361.bmp\} \tab \b \i double click by right mouse button \i0 \b0 \par
\par
The \b \i click \i0 \b0 and \b \i double click by mouse button \i0 \b0 elements serve to test the fact, whether the relevant mouse button has been pressed. The flag of clicking does not depend on the fact that the key has been released in the meantime. The flag is reset after each test. When clicking with the mouse button for the first time only the click flag is set. If the following click is carried out during a sufficiently short time interval (depending on the mouse feature setting in the Windows system settings), the mouse double click flag is set, too.\par
\par
{\uldb \{bmc IDF20362.bmp\}\tab mouse test in the region}{\v 20362} \par
{\uldb \{bmc IDF20404.bmp\}\tab setting shape of mouse cursor}{\v 20404} \par
\par
\i \b Note: \b0 During the program run the inalterability of the mouse data is ensured till the next moment of the {\uldb waiting}{\v 20122} service. This concerns above all the mouse cursor position and the key pressing.\i0 \par
\par
\page

